        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 5:08PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 507 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Ovando, or 16 miles north of Drummond, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ovando.

This includes Highway 200 E between mile markers 40 and 54.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
